      </mri:citation>
      <mri:abstract>
        <gco:CharacterString>&lt;a href="https://doi.org/10.57745/C5UQ2X" target="_blank"&gt;Lien vers les données&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;UDG
          enzyme-MD simulation. &lt;br&gt; Initially, the UDG enzyme was solvated using the TIP3P water model, and 0.15
          M sodium and chloride ions were added to neutralize the system. &lt;br&gt; Before running the production MD,
          minimization and equilibration steps were performed on the UDG enzyme. The final MD production run was
          conducted on the system for 500 ns to obtain a stable configuration. &lt;br&gt; The 'input' folder contains
          the files necessary to run the simulation, while the 'output' folder contains the resulting trajectory.
        </gco:CharacterString>
      </mri:abstract>
